ia":"","overlay-type":"","overlay-color":"","overlay-opacity":"","overlay-gradient":""}},"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[6],"tags":[171,336,163,503,510,114,624,826,22,103],"class_list":["post-25457","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-wisdom-al-hikmah","tag-ablution-wudu","tag-cleanliness-al-taharah","tag-fiqh","tag-imam-ahmad-ibn-hanbal","tag-imam-ash-shafiee","tag-manners-adab","tag-menstruation-al-hayd","tag-al-mushaf","tag-al-quran","tag-women-al-nisa"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-6CB","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":25509,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/wudu-fingers-through-beard\/","url_meta":{"origin":25457,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Running fingers through thick beard in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would run his fingers through his beard during ablution. Al-Tirmidhi said, \"According to this, the majority of the people of knowledge among the companions of the Prophet, and those after them, hold the opinion that fingers should be\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14904,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/10\/suhur-recite-fifty-ayat\/","url_meta":{"origin":25457,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Suhur: Prolonging pre-fasting meal before Fajr","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 10, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Thabit reported: We ate the pre-fasting meal\u00a0with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and then we stood for prayer. It was asked, \u201cHow long was it between the two calls to prayer?\u201d Zayd said, \u201cIt was time enough to recite fifty verses from the Quran.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25443,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/25\/hadith-on-water-pure-water-is-always-clean-and-can-be-used-for-ablution\/","url_meta":{"origin":25457,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Taharah: Water is pure unless change in smell, taste, color","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 25, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWater is pure for ablution and nothing makes it impure.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 66 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Imam Ahmad Al-Bayhaqi said, \u201cWater is pure unless an impurity falls into it that changes its\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25653,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/20\/wipe-non-leather-socks-sandals\/","url_meta":{"origin":25457,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping over non-leather socks, sandals","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 20, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Mughirah ibn Shu\u2019bah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, performed ablution by wiping over non-leather socks and sandals. Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cIt is the view of more than one of the scholars, as is said by Sufyan al-Thawri, Ibn al-Mubarak, Al-Shafi\u2019i, Ahmad, and Ishaq. They said one may\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4098,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/04\/ahmad-sunnah-tafseer-quran\/","url_meta":{"origin":25457,"position":4},"title":"Ahmad on Tafsir: The Sunnah is exegesis, explanation of Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 4, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Fadl ibn Ziyad reported: I heard Ahmad Ibn Hanbal, may Allah have mercy on him, respond to a question on the opinion that the Sunnah overrules the Quran. Ahmad said, \u201cI do not dare say that. Rather, the Sunnah is the explanation of the Book and its clarification.\u201d Source: al-Bah\u0323r\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4008,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/03\/shafiee-contemplate-surah-asr\/","url_meta":{"origin":25457,"position":5},"title":"Shafi\u2019i on Quran: Enough to contemplate upon Surat al-&#8216;Asr","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Kathir reported: Al-Shafi\u2019i, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIf the people were to reflect upon Surat al-'Asr, it would be enough for them.\u201d Source: Tafsi\u0304r Ibn Kathi\u0304r\u00a0103:1 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0643\u062b\u064a\u0631 \u0648\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0634\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0641\u0650\u0639\u0650\u064a\u064f\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u062d\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0648\u0652 \u062a\u064e\u062f\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0651\u0631\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0633\u064f \u0647\u064e\u0630\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064f\u0651\u0648\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0633\u0650\u0639\u064e\u062a\u0652\u0647\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u00a0103:1 \u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0638\u064a\u0645 \u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631 \u0633\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0635\u0631","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25457","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=25457"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25457\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=25457"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"hre